  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Socrates
Lived:         470 - -399
Nationality:   Greek
Field:         Philosophy
Known For:     Socratic method
Contribution:  Father of Western philosophy; sentenced to death; documented by Plato
Quote:         "The only true wisdom is knowing you know nothing."

Name:          Marie Curie
Lived:         1867 - 1934
Nationality:   Polish-French
Field:         Chemistry/Physics
Known For:     Radioactivity
Contribution:  First woman Nobel laureate; Nobel in two sciences; discovered radium and polonium
Quote:         "Nothing in life is to be feared, only to be understood."

Name:          Stephen Hawking
Lived:         1942 - 2018
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Black hole radiation
Contribution:  Proved black holes emit radiation; A Brief History of Time; communicated science publicly
Quote:         "Intelligence is the ability to adapt to change."

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Law of Large Numbers
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      Sample mean converges to expected value
Applications: Insurance, gambling, statistics
Discoverer:   Jacob Bernoulli (1713)

Theorem/Law:  Golden Ratio
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 = 1.618...
Applications: Art, architecture, nature, design
Discoverer:   Ancient Greeks (500)

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

